# TypeScript & React Conventions

- Use path alias `@/` for imports (e.g. `@/lib/constants`, `@/features/budget/presentation`)
- Prefer functional components; extract logic to custom hooks
- Colocate types with modules; export interfaces/types used elsewhere
- Use Zod for form validation with react-hook-form + @hookform/resolvers
- Run `npm run typecheck` and `npm run lint` before completing changes

## Store & data flow

- Zustand stores in `src/features/*/infrastructure/store.ts`; avoid importing store in `lib/` (keep lib pure)
- Budget CRUD and load/save live in `features/budget/infrastructure/store.ts`; session/key state in `features/session/infrastructure/store.ts`
